As of the [[census|census]]<ref name ="FactFinder">{{cite web|title=American FactFinder|url=http://factfinder2.census.gov/faces/nav/jsf/pages/index.xhtml|publisher=[[United_States_Census_Bureau|United States Census Bureau]]|accessdate=2013-01-25}}</ref> of 2010, there were 7,102 people, 3,852 households, and 1,784 families residing in the town. The [[population_density|population density]] was {{convert|1610.4|PD/sqmi|PD/km2|1}}. There were 30,119 housing units at an average density of {{convert|6829.7|/sqmi|/km2|1}}. The racial makeup of the town was 92.2% [[White_(U.S._Census)|White]], 2.7% [[African_American_(U.S._Census)|African American]], 0.2% [[Native_American_(U.S._Census)|Native American]], 1.3% [[Asian_(U.S._Census)|Asian]], 2.2% from [[Race_(U.S._Census)|other races]], and 1.4% from two or more races. [[Hispanic_(U.S._Census)|Hispanic]] or [[Latino_(U.S._Census)|Latino]] of any race were 5.9% of the population.

